Now here is where it gets spicy,  quick quick quick — let me rapid-fire through this.

2
00:00:07,039 --> 00:00:19,934
But here's where it gets really interesting,  EOS has overhead: each transaction requires a round-trip to the transaction coordinator for begin, commit, and abort.

3
00:00:19,934 --> 00:00:26,986
Throughput drops approximately 20-thirty percent compared to non-transactional producers.

4
00:00:26,986 --> 00:00:40,197
Tune transaction.timeout.ms (default 60 s) to match your batch processing time — transactions that exceed this timeout are automatically aborted by the broker.

5
00:00:40,197 --> 00:00:48,105
Real talk: Flipkart's Big Billion Day crashed their servers THREE times before they got this right.

